news.title: CapitaLand India Trust acquires 2.5 million sq ft from Phoenix Group in Hyderabad
news.para: CapitaLand India Trust will provide funding of Rs 2.15 billion (S$34.68 million) to refinance the existing loan and receive interest on the funding at a rate which is higher than its borrowing cost.

news.title: Godrej Properties' net profit increases by 5.32% in Q4 FY24
news.para: Godrej Properties' net total consolidated income stood at Rs 1,914.82 crore in Q4 FY24, a growth of 4.13 per cent from Rs 1,838.82 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Shriram Properties acquires four acre land parcel in Bengaluru
news.para: Shriram Properties will develop a residential project encompassing around four lakh sq ft of aggregate saleable area. This project has revenue potential of over Rs 250 crore.

news.title: Mysuru civic body collects 46% property tax in April
news.para: According to MCC sources, officials of all nine zones have collected Rs 91.5 crore in property tax as against the target of Rs 199.9 crore for this fiscal year.

news.title: Brick by brick, Pirojsha changed the realty game at Godrej
news.para: Pirojsha Godrej's strategic leadership at Godrej Properties during the global financial crisis led to innovative approaches like joint developments and a capital-lite model. His focus on efficiency and immediate project launches propels the company's growth.

news.title: Banks homing in on a bigger share of expanding real estate pie
news.para: The real estate sector is growing across segments said property analysts. Top seven property markets in the country registered total sales of 74,486 apartments during the quarter.

news.title: Max Estates to jointly develop 18.23 acres land in Gurugram
news.para: This land parcel is contiguous to its existing 11.80 acres of land on Dwarka Expressway in sector 36 A, Gurugram on which Max Estates had done a joint development agreement (JDA) last year.

news.title: Embassy Group sales bookings up 85% to Rs 2,250 crore in FY24
news.para: ​In a statement, the company said it achieved best-ever performance in the 2023-24 fiscal year for its residential business, with sales transaction value of Rs 2,250 crore -- an 85.5 per cent jump from the preceding year.

news.title: China property shares extends gains after government highlights clearing inventory
news.para: The Hang Seng Mainland Properties Index rose 4% in the morning session to a more than four-month high, with China Vanke and Longfor Group jumping 10% and 7.8%, respectively.

news.title: Evictions surge in Arizona with housing shortage and rising prices
news.para: Maricopa is home to Phoenix, one of the fastest growing cities in the United States, a place where rents have skyrocketed since the start of the Covid-19 pandemic, leaving an ever-increasing number of people in trouble.

news.title: SM-REIT to create monetisation opportunity of Rs 70,000 crore: ICRA
news.para: ​In November last year, the Sebi board cleared the amendments to the REITs Regulations, 2014, in order to create a regulatory framework for the facilitation of SM REITs, with an asset value of at least Rs 50 crore vis-a-vis minimum asset value of Rs 500 crore for existing REITs.

news.title: Godrej camps can’t compete for six years, except in real estate business
news.para: Both groups can use the brand name in the real estate development & marketing business. Jamshyd and Smita have interests in real estate through the unlisted Godrej & Boyce while Adi and Nadir control the listed Godrej Properties.

news.title: Construction sector entities’ revenues to grow by 12-15% in FY25: Icra
news.para: ICRA maintains a stable outlook on the sector with steady growth in operating income, moderate leverage, and healthy coverage metrics.

news.title: The Executive Centre India aims to achieve 10-15% revenue in FY25
news.para: The total adjusted EBITDA for 2023 was USD 19 million (Rs 159 crore) for TEC India. It delivered 31% growth in revenue over last year and contributed 26% to the overall adjusted EBITDA. TEC India achieved a 35% growth in EBITDA over last year.

news.title: No attachment of properties under PMLA after acquittal in scheduled offence: Delhi HC
news.para: The Delhi High Court has held that no proceedings under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA), including attachment of properties, can continue after the accused is acquitted in the predicate offence even if an appeal against it is pending.

news.title: New condo in Mumbai's old neighbourhood combo deal commands highest price
news.para: In Mumbai, the real estate landscape is evolving with a shift towards modern amenities in new luxury condos. High prices in prime locations like Carmichael Road and Walkeshwar Road reflect the demand for upscale living in the city.

news.title: Lenders seek RBI clearance to sell Jaiprakash Associates loan to NARCL
news.para: SBI-led lenders seek RBI approval to transfer JAL's ₹18,000 crore debt to NARCL for a ₹10,000 crore acquisition, impacting IBC processes and NCLT resolutions. Dalmia Cement offers ₹5,666 crore for JAL's units amid ongoing litigations.

news.title: Kalpataru to redevelop four acre housing society in Mumbai
news.para: Kalpataru Ltd acquires rights for housing society redevelopment in Lokhandwala, Mumbai with significant revenue potential. Multiple redevelopment projects in progress in Mumbai suburbs. Market achieves record highs despite rising property prices.
